Classification.Comment: The c.1869_1902del34 pathogenic mutation, located in coding exon 9 of the BRCA1 gene, results from a deletion of 34 nucleotides at nucleotide positions 1869 to 1902, causing a translational frameshift with a predicted alternate stop codon. This alteration is expected to result in loss of function by premature protein truncation or nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. As such, this alteration is interpreted as a disease-causing mutation.
